text: 115.2. LRU Cache Replacement Assume you are given a tiny 4-element, fully-associative cache that uses LRU replacement. The cache stores single byte values (i.e., a line is a single byte). If the cache is empty at the beginning of execution, how many misses will the following string of accesses produce? G,D0,G,C,A,G,D,A,C,G,D,B,E,A,B,B,A,G,E,B integer misses @ Save & Grade Single attempt Additional attempts available with new variants @
